"i18n:UserDef.kAcceptLeadingIntonations.description" = "This feature accommodates certain typing mistakes that the intonation mark might be typed at first (which is sequentially wrong from a common sense that intonation marks are supposed to be used for confirming combinations). It won't work if the current parser is of (any) pinyin. Also, this feature won't work when an intonation override is possible (and enabled).";
"i18n:UserDef.kAcceptLeadingIntonations.shortTitle" = "Accept leading intonations in rare cases";
"i18n:UserDef.kAllowRescoringSingleKanjiCandidates.description" = "⚠️💀 This may hinder the sentence-composition algorithm from giving appropriate results. You are urged to turn this switch off at all costs, unless you really know what you are doing.";
"i18n:UserDef.kAllowRescoringSingleKanjiCandidates.shortTitle" = "Allow boosting / excluding a candidate of single kanji";
